<page_title>Using a model container to play animated GIF files</page_title>
<text> Using a model container to play animated GIF files

Did you know that you can a 2D model container to play an animated GIF file? Any 2D model container has a built-in animated GIF player that can be used to show a multiple-frame GIF file, as demonstrated by the following example:

 
  

Note that you need to insert a particle in order to make this work, because the model container will not run if there is no particle in it.</text>
